YouTube Comment Scraper
A simple Python tool that uses Selenium to scrape comments from YouTube videos.
Features

Extracts comment author names, text content, and like counts
Saves collected data to CSV format for easy analysis

Requirements

Python 3.6 or higher
Firefox browser installed
Selenium WebDriver
geckodriver (Firefox WebDriver executable)

Limitations
YouTube may change its page structure, requiring selector updates
Scraping too many comments quickly might trigger rate limiting
Comments with special formatting may not extract perfectly